<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,983,1330]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,326,983,1009]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Observations:</emphasis>
Over the last two decades, a series of karyotypic studies conducted in different apparently isolated populations assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pflaumer" authorityYear="1944" box="[514,666,1024,1049]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis box="[514,666,1024,1049]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">L. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have suggested that they might have experienced processes of genetic diversification (
<bibRefCitation author="Lamborot, M. &amp; Espinoza, A. &amp; Alvarez, E. E." box="[427,680,1064,1090]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="593 - 595" refId="ref63362" refString="Lamborot, M., Espinoza, A. &amp; Alvarez, E. E. (1979) Karyotypic variation in Chilean lizards of the genus Liolaemus (Iguanidae). Experientia, 35, 593 - 595." type="journal article" year="1979">
Lamborot 
<emphasis box="[552,611,1064,1089]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
1979
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamborot, M. &amp; Alvarez-Starret, E. &amp; Campos, I. &amp; Espinoza, A." box="[692,753,1064,1090]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="328 - 334" refId="ref63128" refString="Lamborot, M., Alvarez-Starret, E., Campos, I. &amp; Espinoza, A. (1981) Karyotypic characterization of three Chilean subspecies of Liolaemus monticola. Journal of Heredity, 72, 328 - 334." type="journal article" year="1981">1981</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamborot, M. &amp; Eaton, L. C. &amp; Carrasco, B." box="[765,827,1064,1090]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="23 - 24" refId="ref63311" refString="Lamborot, M., Eaton, L. C. &amp; Carrasco, B. (2003) The Aconcagua river as another barrier to Liolaemus monticola (Sauria: Iguanidae) chromosomal races of central Chile. Revista Chilena de Historia Natural, 76, 23 - 24." type="journal article" year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamborot, M." box="[839,1036,1064,1090]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="70" refId="ref62824" refString="Lamborot, M. (1985 a) Rios como barrera al flujo genico en poblaciones naturales de Liolaemus monticola Muller and Hellmich (Iguanidae). Archivos de Biologia y Medicina Experimentales, 18, R- 70." type="journal article" year="1985">
Lamborot 1985 
<bibRefCitation author="Arujo, A. F. B." box="[1023,1036,1064,1090]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="857 - 865" refId="ref51071" refString="Arujo, A. F. B. (1991) Structure of a white sand-dune lizard community of coastal Brazil. Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 51, 857 - 865." type="journal article" year="1991">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, b, 1991, 1993, 1998, 2001; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamborot, M. &amp; Eaton, L." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="189 - 200" refId="ref63216" refString="Lamborot, M. &amp; Eaton, L. (1992) Concordance of morphological variation and chromosomal races of Liolaemus monticola (Tropiduridae) separated by riverine barriers in the Andes. Zeitschrift fuer Zoologische Systematik und Evolutionsforschung, 30, 189 - 200." type="journal article" year="1992">Lamborot &amp; Eaton 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamborot, M. &amp; Eaton, L. C." box="[410,472,1104,1130]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="105 - 111" refId="ref63262" refString="Lamborot, M. &amp; Eaton, L. C. (1997) The Maipo River as a biogeographical barrier to Liolaemus monticola (Tropiduridae) in the mountain ranges of central Chile. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research, 35, 105 - 111." type="journal article" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamborot, M. &amp; Alvarez-Sarret, E." box="[487,891,1104,1130]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="435 - 449" refId="ref63083" refString="Lamborot, M. &amp; Alvarez-Sarret, E. (1993) Karyotypic variation within and between populations of Liolaemus monticola (Tropiduridae) separated by the Maipo River in the coastal range of central Chile. Herpetologica, 49, 435 - 449." type="journal article" year="1993">Lamborot &amp; Alvarez-Sarret 1993</bibRefCitation>
). Nevertheless, although karyological aspects have been explored thoroughly, additional detailed studies are needed to evaluate the impact of geographical barriers, such as rivers, in driving incipient differentiation in these lizard populations (Núñez &amp; Pincheira- Donoso 2006; see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamborot, M. &amp; Eaton, L." box="[366,654,1224,1250]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="189 - 200" refId="ref63216" refString="Lamborot, M. &amp; Eaton, L. (1992) Concordance of morphological variation and chromosomal races of Liolaemus monticola (Tropiduridae) separated by riverine barriers in the Andes. Zeitschrift fuer Zoologische Systematik und Evolutionsforschung, 30, 189 - 200." type="journal article" year="1992">Lamborot &amp; Eaton 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamborot, M. &amp; Eaton, L. C." box="[665,727,1224,1250]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="105 - 111" refId="ref63262" refString="Lamborot, M. &amp; Eaton, L. C. (1997) The Maipo River as a biogeographical barrier to Liolaemus monticola (Tropiduridae) in the mountain ranges of central Chile. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research, 35, 105 - 111." type="journal article" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
